description:
Cal Poly is a recognized leader throughout industry due to our “Learn by Doing” motto. Taking this concept to the extreme, Formula SAE creates a true engineering business dedicated to the production and marketing of a fast, safe, and efficient race car. The Formula SAE competition is an event hosted by the Society of Automotive Engineers to test cars built by students for the non-professional weekend racer. Over four days we compete against nearly 100 colleges and universities from around the world. Judges from industry evaluate us based on engineering design, production cost and business plan. Dynamic events measure handling, acceleration, reliability and fuel economy. 

Our team is comprised of Cal Poly students who have a passion for engineering and learning – with the Team Lead and Team Manager at the top, a Technical Director managing the engineering projects and sub-team leads responsible for individual designs and other functions.
